# ==============================================================================
# NOTES & COMMENTS
# ==============================================================================

# This .gitignore prioritizes security by preventing:
# ‚úÖ Credential leaks (passwords, API keys, tokens)
# ‚úÖ SSH key exposure
# ‚úÖ Database connection strings
# ‚úÖ Personal information
# ‚úÖ Large binary files
# ‚úÖ Temporary/cache files
# ‚úÖ IDE-specific configurations
#
# Best Practices:
# 1. Never commit real credentials
# 2. Use environment variables for secrets
# 3. Add .env.example with dummy values
# 4. Review files before committing
# 5. Use git secrets/pre-commit hooks
#
# To check what's being ignored:
#   git status --ignored
#
# To force add an ignored file (use cautiously):
#   git add -f filename
#
# ==============================================================================

